# AGENTS.md

This project uses the **Agent Norms** — its working conventions live as files under `agent/`, committed alongside the code and read at the start of each session.

## Rules — `agent/rules/`

**Read every file in `agent/rules/` at the start of a session and follow them.** They override default behavior where they conflict; explicit user instructions still win.

`agent/rules/` is organized by package (`foundation/`, `testing/`, …), each installed with `git subtree`. The framework itself — what the `agent/` directories are and how to work with them (`rules`, `observations`, `deferred`, `log`, and the `plans` / `design` / `experiments` work artifacts) — is defined by the **`foundation`** package's own rules. Read those first; everything else builds on them.

